e) The emergency response plan;

In the event of an emergency involving a flammable mixture, it is facility policy to dial 911 to notify the appropriate emergency response department and request assistance.  In the event of a fire emergency, the Carlyss or Sulphur Fire Department is directly notified.  This policy is only used when no other emergency assistance (medical, etc) is required.

f) Planned changes to improve safety;

Southern Ionics recently conducted a review of the Process Hazard Analysis.  No deficiencies were found during the analysis; however, Southern Ionics noted several areas that will be reviewed more closely for potential safety improvements.  Detailed findings of this review are in the Process Hazard Analysis dated January 8, 2024.
